7. RESPONSIBLE DISCLOSURE
If you accidentally discover a vulnerability while using this tool on authorized systems:

Stop immediately – Do not exploit further

Document your findings – What you found, when, how

Contact the owner/administrator – Privately and professionally

Give reasonable time – For them to fix it (typically 30-90 days)

Do not share publicly – Until the issue is resolved

This is called responsible disclosure and is the ethical way to handle findings.

